                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 5315/289.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Chargé <persName type="from">Fletcher</persName> to the <gloss
                            type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraphrase.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Peking</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1909-06-24">
                            <hi rend="italic">June 24, 1909</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Mr. Fletcher reports that Liang has informed him that he has notified the
                    representatives of the groups here that the loan will not be concluded unless
                    the bankers settle with the American group; adds that Liang hopes matter can be
                    speedily adjusted; that United States will be content with equal financial
                    participation in this instance and not insist on equal right to furnish
                    material.</p>
            </div>
        </body>
